Rutherford County officials are examining the competing solid waste companies about proposed services. The commissioners hired Caldwell Environmental Solutions LLC for about $50000 to examine proposals.

The public works committee has examined the following six proposals:

Design This LLC of Christiana: provide residential solid waste hauling services and convert the waste to electrical energy; public education on solid waste;

provide residential solid waste hauling services and convert the waste to electrical energy; public education on solid waste; WasteAway of Morrison: dispose of residential waste in a building; convert waste to a composting material or a pellet that can be used as an EPA approved fuel source for coal-burning; separate valuable recycling from waste;

dispose of residential waste in a building; convert waste to a composting material or a pellet that can be used as an EPA approved fuel source for coal-burning; separate valuable recycling from waste; Rockwood Sustainable Solutions of Lebanon: operate a transfer station on county land on Florence Road by CSX railroad lines to haul trash out of county; landfill of construction and demolition materials; composting including wood from construction and demolition waste;

operate a transfer station on county land on Florence Road by CSX railroad lines to haul trash out of county; landfill of construction and demolition materials; composting including wood from construction and demolition waste; Waste Revaluation of Stanley North Dakota: Reclaim county's two closed landfills adjacent to Middle Point Landfill; accept waste to convert to energy; composting; recycling;

Reclaim county's two closed landfills adjacent to Middle Point Landfill; accept waste to convert to energy; composting; recycling; Waste Alliance of Murfreesboro: proposes to make arrangements with vendors to recycle and compost; public education on solid waste;

proposes to make arrangements with vendors to recycle and compost; public education on solid waste; Straightway Enterprises of Columbia: recycling composting Collection of solid waste at centers: transportation of solid waste out of county; reclaiming county's two closed landfills on 75 acres located near Middle Point Landfill; residential solid waste pick up; disposal of batteries oil paint antifreeze and electronics; disposal of household hazardous waste; disposal of furniture mattresses tires and other problem waste; disposal of construction and demolition materials; public education on solid waste.

The committee will examine three other solid waste companies:

Republic Services of Phoenix at 5:30 p.m. May 12: disposal of trash at Middle Point Landfill; collection services at county's 15 centers that accept recycling including 14 that accept trash; long-term reclamation of county's 75 acres of closed landfills on 288 acres; composting; recycling; residential solid waste hauling services; disposal of Batteries oil paint antifreeze and electronics; disposal of household hazardous waste; disposal of furniture mattresses tires and other problem waste; disposal of construction and demolition materials; transportation of recycling materials out of county); public education on solid waste;

